taffof all Parisian bistros - was organised in front of the Paristown hallon Sunday 24 March.\n\nDozens of participants set off carrying a plate with a croissant,coffeeand a glass ofwaterfor a 1.2 mile-long route through the Marais neighborhood in central Paris.\n\nAn essential element of Parisian heritage, bistros are at the heart of the effort to promote the Parisian way of life and attract visitors during the Olympics.\n\n04:10\n\n02:59\n\n00:50\n\n01:20\n\n05:16\n\n09:16\n\n40:26\n\n06:56\n\n07:03\n\n05:30\n\n05:37\n\n45:14\n\n14:11\n\n12:18\n\n30:24\n\n16:08\n\n17:41\n\n18:22\n\n13:43\n\n12:41\n\n41:50\n\n48:45\n\n40:57\n\n37:44\n\n56:37\n\n58:53\n\n41:30\n\n56:09\n\n07:11\n\n08:32\n\n05:45\n\n05:35\n\n08:02\n\n06:42\n\n05:23\n\n07:08\n\n07:40\n\n08:56\n\n13:49\n\n10:57\n\n07:53\n\n19:31\n\n04:07\n\n11:19\n\n02:50\n\nSponsored\n\n03:09\n\nSponsored\n\n02:39\n\nSponsored\n\n01:53\n\nSponsored\n\n01:39\n\nSponsored\n\n02:40\n\nSponsored\n\n07:30\n\n07:54\n\n05:23\n\n05:35\n\n09:47\n\n06:28\n\n06:23\n\n07:35\n\n08:03\n\n11:54\n\n08:21\n\n06:38\n\n07:25\n\n04:31\n\n07:30\n\n03:34\n\n13:23\n\n17:05\n\n03:51\n\n04:18\n\n06:26\n\n04:30\n\n03:35\n\n03:45\n\n02:03\n\n03:22\n\n02:15\n\n02:22\n\n02:21\n\n01:43\n\n01:42\n\n01:45\n\n10:44\n\n03:44\n\n07:42\n\n09:22\n\n06:11\n\n07:50\n\n06:21\n\n02:19\n\n10:42\n\n06:27\n\n07:23\n\n06:35\n\n12:18\n\n11:50\n\n09:03\n\n13:07\n\n02:10\n\n00:45\n\n01:05\n\n00:42\n\n00:36\n\n00:33\n\n00:35\n\n00:57\n\n00:14\n\n03:03\n\n00:21\n\n01:10\n\n00:20\n\n00:57\n\n00:17\n\n00:31\n\n00:49\n\n00:33\n\n01:00\n\n00:31\n\n00:54\n\n01:08\n\n01:35\n\n00:47\n\n01:19\n\n02:33\n\n00:23\n\n00:22\n\n00:59\n\n01:23\n\n00:28\n\n00:27\n\n03:29\n\n03:07\n\n03:07\n\n03:24\n\n01:36\n\n00:42\n\n01:26\n\n00:32\n\n00:31\n\n02:00\n\n00:40\n\n00:58\n\n04:23\n\n04:26\n\n01:01\n\n01:07\n\n15:55\n\n16:33\n\n16:06\n\n15:01\n\n15:16\n\n01:16\n\n00:36\n\n00:48\n\n01:08\n\n01:12\n\n01:23\n\n01:24\n\nLive\n\nPlease refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in", "title": "Watch: Paris waiters battle it out in revived croissant race | Lifestyle | Independent TV", "top-image": "https://cdn.jwplayer.com/v2/media/hiTziLha/poster.jpg?width=720", "domain": "www.independent.co.uk", "lang": "en", "author": "", "description": "A tradition dating back to 1914 has been revived in Paris as the French capital prepares to welcome the Olympic Games this summer. The waiter’s race - open to the staff of all Parisian bistros - was organised in front of the Paris town hall on Sunday 24 March. Dozens of participants set off carrying a plate with a croissant, coffee and a glass of water for a 1.2 mile-long route through the Marais neighborhood in central Paris. An essential element of Parisian heritage, bistros are at the heart of the effort to promote the Parisian way of life and attract visitors during the Olympics.", "keywords": ""}